{"word":"ἁμός 2","slug":"ἁμός 2","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n5447\" key=\"a(mo/s2\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ἁμός</orth> (B), <pron extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pron\">[ᾰ]</pron>, old word equiv. to <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">τις</itype>, only in <pos opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pos\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Adv.\">Adv.</a></pos> forms <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἁμοῦ, ἁμῆ, ἁμοῖ, ἁμῶς, ἁμόθεν, ἁμόθι,</foreign> and in compds. as <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">οὐδαμός,</foreign> Hdn.Gr.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:169\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.169</biblScope></bibl>. (<sense id=\"n5447.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">sṃ-,</tr_> cf. Goth. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">sums (some one), suman (sometime, once).</tr_>)</sense> </entryFree>"}]}